<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-7005] Compile bug with @Synchronized(&quot;lockname&quot;) and undefined lockname</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-7005</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using &lt;tt&gt;@Synchronized(&apos;mylock&apos;)&lt;/tt&gt;, but failing to declare &lt;tt&gt;mylock&lt;/tt&gt; in class, compile fails with bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; groovy.transform.*

    @CompileStatic
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;A {
        @Synchronized(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;mylock&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
        void sync() {
        }
       
    }

    def a = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; A()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Typical error :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;BUG! exception in phase &apos;canonicalization&apos; in source unit &apos;/path/to/test.groovy&apos; unexpected NullpointerException&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12817765">GROOVY-7005</key>
